cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper explores the Graph Convolutional Network architecture and its variations for improving performance on several datasets. This work falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with developing and improving a neural network architecture. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph regularization and alternative graph convolution approaches, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The datasets used in the experiments are related to information retrieval and natural language processing, which are subfields of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
